In Excel, when you open a file, there’s a tab at the bottom that says “Sheet 1.” If you are going to work on multiple spreadsheets in the same document, you can open Sheet 2, 3, etc. and you can give each sheet a name. The only concession to accuracy is that a file may contain many sheets. 

To someone who has used Excel extensively, this is not a stretch at all.

@retired, with cat

The icon labeled Sheets is the Google knockoff of Excel. But the tab thing is true about Excel. 

And although it’s a spreadsheet program, each individual one is commonly called a sheet.

