@Tom

Huh? You are welcome to come here at any point in your solving journey and make a comment. Simply reference the clue number – i.e., 1A or 1D – or even better, the clue itself, in brackets. For example, [Word before baked or naked].

As for whether or not other solvers have commented about a particular clue (or answer), use the search box at the top of the comments and you'll see any and all mentions of your search term.

@Tom
I'm guessing you're a newer solver, and I'm guessing you're solving in the app. I'm inferring from "...easier to comment" that you find it frustrating to have to leave the puzzle mid-solve in order to get to Wordplay and the comments--there are multiple steps both getting there and then getting back to the puzzle. That was a relatively recent change to the app, and one that has been almost universally decried by solvers. There is a work-around: open wordplay in your browser, and then you can toggle back and forth between browser and app as needed.

I look forward to hearing your thoughts on various clues. Welcome to Wordplay.

